column1039: More pre fire: 49.7 TSHE cones, 70.7 LAOC cones

Moderate burn severity. Small trees dead, large trees alive. Tons of this year seedlings. Many were similar but hard to ID, likeY PSME All LAOC and TSHE are correct. LAOC, PSME, PICO, TSHE cones all present, PICO cones less abundant. PIMO seedlings based on pinwheel cotyl.
Only measured prefire on 1,3,4. 2nd tree core: PSME, HT = 18 m, DBH = 25.9

80% confident about PICO seedlings, but could not locate a seed source. Could be out of its uphill. One 2 yr seedling found outside transects that could be PIEN or PSME. One seedling in transect that may have been PSME, it had pointed reddish bud, but serrulate margins. We measured 3 downed trees that were clearly alive during fire. BEPA was leaning. Many old standing PSME that were dead during fire. 2nd tree core PIEN 22 m tall, 241 mm DBH

Nearly even larch stand, some mostly under PIEN. Again, apparently PICO seedlings but no seed source visible. Fireweed, arnica, Moss.
